{"ID":270206, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"206\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs205.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs207.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 206<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">to acknowledge this principle, it is evident from the multifarious creeds and notions concerning this\n  matter that they understand nothing of this principle, and it is equally as plain that without a divine\n  communication they must remain in ignorance. The world always mistook false prophets<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> for true\n  ones, and those that were sent of God, they considered to be false prophets and hence they killed,\n  stoned, punished and imprisoned the true prophets, and these had to hide themselves &ldquo;in deserts and\n  dens, and caves of the earth,&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> and though the most honorable men of the earth,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> they banished them\n  from their society as vagabonds, whilst they cherished, honored and supported knaves, vagabonds,\n  hypocrites, impostors, and the basest of men.<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Gift of Discernment of Spirits<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">A man must have the discerning of spirits,<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> as we before stated, to understand these things, and\n  how is he to obtain this gift if there are no gifts of the Spirit? And how can these gifts be obtained\n  without revelation?<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> &ldquo;Christ ascended into heaven, and gave gifts to men;<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> and He gave some\n  Apostles, and some Prophets, and some Evangelists, and some Pastors and Teachers.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> And how\n  were Apostles, Prophets, Pastors, Teachers and Evangelists chosen?<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> By prophecy (revelation) and\n  by laying on of hands<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span>&mdash;by a divine communication, and a divinely appointed ordinance&mdash;through\n  the medium of the Priesthood, organized according to the order of God,<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> by divine appointment.<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span>\n  The Apostles in ancient times held the keys of this Priesthood<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span>&mdash;of the mysteries of the Kingdom<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span>\n  of God, and consequently were enabled to unlock and unravel all things pertaining to the\n  government of the Church,<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> the welfare of society, the future destiny of men, and the agency, power\n  and influence of spirits; for they could control them at pleasure, bid them depart in the name of\n  Jesus,<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> and detect their mischievous and mysterious operations when trying to palm themselves\n  upon the Church in a religious garb, and militate against the interest of the Church and spread of\n  truth. We read that they &ldquo;cast out devils in the name of Jesus,&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> and when a woman possessing the\n  spirit of divination, cried before Paul and Silas, &ldquo;these are the servants of the Most High God that\n  show unto us the way of salvation,&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> they detected the spirit. And although she spake favorably of\n  them, Paul commanded the spirit come out of her, and saved themselves from the opprobrium<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107881\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107881)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107881)\">Matt. 7:15<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110290\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110290)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110290)\">Heb. 11:38<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111228\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111228)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111228)\">2 Ne. 15:13<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114470\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114470)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114470)\">D&amp;C 76:75<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115222\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115222)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115222)\">D&amp;C 101:73<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112499\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112499)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112499)\">Hel. 13:24-28<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109526\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109526)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109526)\">1 Cor. 12:10<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113919\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113919)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113919)\">D&amp;C 46:23<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113927\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113927)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113927)\">D&amp;C 46:27<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">7. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109802\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109802)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109802)\">Eph. 4:8<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">8. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109806\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109806)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109806)\">Eph. 4:11<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">9. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108834\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108834)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108834)\">John 15:16<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">10. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110018\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110018)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110018)\">1 Tim. 4:14<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111819\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111819)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111819)\">Alma 6:1<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117197\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 117197)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(117197)\">A of F 1:5<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">11. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111777\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111777)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111777)\">Alma 4:20<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114625\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114625)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114625)\">D&amp;C 84:18<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">12. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116398\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116398)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116398)\">D&amp;C 132:26,40<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116975\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116975)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116975)\">Abr. 1:4<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">13. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116189\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116189)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116189)\">D&amp;C 128:20<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117149\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 117149)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(117149)\">JS&mdash;H 1:72<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">14. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108001\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108001)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108001)\">Matt. 13:11<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114215\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114215)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114215)\">D&amp;C 64:5<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">15. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115260\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115260)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115260)\">D&amp;C 102:8<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">16. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109122\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109122)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109122)\">Acts 16:18<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">17. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108384\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108384)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108384)\">Mark 16:17<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">18. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109115\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109115)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109115)\">Acts 16:16-18<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n  <\/div>\n<\/div>"}